    },
    {
      "id": "sybil_2_listing_2",
      "firm_id": "sybil_2",
      "description": "Available for acquisition is a mechanically sound 2003 BMW M3 (E46) featuring the high-revving S54 3.2L inline-six engine. This power unit utilizes individual throttle bodies and a high-pressure Double VANOS variable valve timing system to achieve a linear power delivery up to its 8,000 RPM redline. The drivetrain is anchored by a Getrag 6-speed manual transmission and a factory-spec limited-slip differential. To ensure structural integrity, the rear subframe has been professionally reinforced\u2014a vital upgrade for this chassis. Recent service includes a comprehensive VANOS overhaul and valve adjustment. While the exterior displays a honest patina indicative of its driver status, the suspension remains tight with refreshed bushings and dampers, preserving the car's legendary steering rack feedback and lateral composure. This is a driver-focused example where mechanical excellence takes precedence over cosmetic perfection.",
      "price": 32500.0,
      "reputation": 0.3,
      "quality": "poor",
      "quality_value": 0.1,
      "timestep_posted": 49
    },
